text.section:
The converting mutual shall give written notice of the right to vote on the plan of conversion to the members of the converting mutual entitled to vote. The notice shall be accompanied by explanatory information concerning the plan of conversion and may be accompanied by proxy solicitation materials. The notice and accompanying information and materials shall not be provided to the members until approved by the commissioner. The notice and accompanying materials shall include:
A brief statement of the subject of the meeting;
The date, time, and location of the meeting;
A description of the member's right to attend and participate in the meeting;
A description of the nature and amount of consideration that will be provided to the eligible members upon completion of the conversion;
If reasonably ascertainable by the converting mutual, a description of the form and amount or approximate amount of consideration to be provided to the particular member to whom the notice is addressed;
A copy of the plan of conversion and summary of the plan; and
A reference to the applicable statutory provisions.
